es/2/jobDescription": "Travel Daily Media is the world’s largest singularly owned B2B digital footprint via E-distribution. With\noperations in Bangkok, Delhi, Dubai and London, our flagship products are Travel Daily Asia, Travel Daily India, Travel Daily Middle East and Travel Daily UK.\nFirst to the market each day with timely breaking news and industry developments, we have collectively 160,000+ active email subscribers to our daily e-newsletters.\nCut through the noise to reach the travel trade in cost effective ways; Travel Daily Media Group is best placed to address your situation and deliver creative integrated solutions quickly and easily because we have an unrivalled portfolio of e-publications\n • trade event sponsorship\n • website takeover \n • banner options\n • supplements \n • digital guides\n • social media channel competitions \n • EDMs to our massive segmented databases\n • training video services\nAll aimed directly at the travel trade to deliver a tightly focused program for you -- created in conjunction with our international team of experts in editorial, advertising and marketing for maximum cost-effectiveness and results to raise awareness of your hotel / airline to the travel trade in Asia and beyond.", "experiences/2/jobEndedOn": "11-2017", "experiences/2/jobLocationCountry": "SG", "experiences/2/jobStartedOn": "11-2016", "experiences/2/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/2/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQEcJ4RMl0j8gQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1719257888282/traveldailyhq_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=LtHFcZqzEz9u8u-cauucQ-MPsfLexOuvhSMSYxMPYU4", "experiences/2/title": "Director Of Business Development", "experiences/3/companyName": "Dewa Phuket", "experiences/3/jobDescription": "Dewa Phuket is a boutique resort with 34 private pool villas and 62 units of one and two bedroom apartments, located on Nai Yang Beach, at the northern end of Phuket island.  Privately owned by a group of individuals with the 62 apartments having condominium status structure with different ownerships, making this an integrated resort.\n\nAs part of the pre-opening team and with direct reporting to the Managing Director, my role was to plan, hire and manage all areas to ensure a successful opening. Following that, I stayed on to ensure the operational efficiency of all the departments.\n\nKey responsibilities:\n-\tDeveloped and implemented standards:  SOPs and P&Ps\n-\tDeveloped website and collateral contents\n-\tBudget planning, cash flow forecasts, sales & marketing planning and P&L management\n-\tProcurement planning\n-\tManaging all aspects of customers feedback and social media forums\n-\tCreating visions for environmental sustainability and policies pertaining to health & safety\n-\tImplementing training plans for all front and back of house\n-\tManaging the operations of the Residence reporting to the Condominium Juristic Person  \n\nAchievements:\n•\tTravelife Gold Sustainability in Tourism\n•\tPlatinum winner – HAPA Signature Serviced Residences (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tPlatinum winner – HAPA Signature Family & Recreational Resort (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tPlatinum winner – HAPA Best Front Office (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tPlatinum winner – HAPA Best Concierge (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tGold winner – HAPA Signature Boutique Hotel/Resort (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tGold winner – HAPA Hospitality Entrepreneur of the Year (best 5 in Asia)\n•\tGold winner- HAPA Luxury Resort (best 10 in Asia)\n•\tTripadvisor Certificate of Excellence Award 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016\n•\tHoliday Check 95% recommendation\n•\tTUI Blue award Bronze 2015\n•\tTUI Blue award Silver 2013", "experiences/3/jobEndedOn": "8-2016", "experiences/3/jobLocation": "Phuket", "experiences/3/jobStartedOn": "8-2008", "experiences/3/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/3/title": "General Manager", "experiences/4/companyId": "330777", "experiences/4/companyIndustry": "Food and Beverage Services", "experiences/4/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/blue-canyon-country-club/", "experiences/4/companyName": "Blue Canyon Country Club", "experiences/4/companySize": "51-200", "experiences/4/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:330777", "experiences/4/companyWebsite": "http://www.bluecanyonclub.com", "experiences/4/jobDescription": "Blue Canyon Country Club is ranked as one of the most prestigious golfing establishments in the region with two international championship courses and hosts to major golfing events. Set within the grounds of this 720 acre valley is a clubhouse with 32 spacious accommodation suites, restaurant, golfers terrace, proshop as well as luxurious locker room facilities for the members and guests of the clubs’ use. Other facilities include the driving range, kiosks, swimming pools and residential condominiums and villas with breathtaking views of the course. \n\nReporting directly to the Chief Operating Officer, I was responsible for the general operation relating to Front Office, Housekeeping, Food & Beverage, Health & Spa, Golf Events Operations and Clubhouse maintenance/repair. In addition to this, I was also responsible for all aspects of the Clubs’ business in the absence of the General Manager.\n\nDuring this period with Blue Canyon, I setup of the Events Operations and Sales Department, which serves to sell Blue Canyon as the golfing venue for potential corporate and incentive groups and oversees all coordination and logistics for the Organizers. \n\nI was also instrumental in the system study and setup for all Front Office and Food and Beverage POS software and assist with the implementation and training of staff. \n\nMy past 5 ½ years with Blue Canyon has been most invaluable and certainly not lacking in dull moments, and the challenges that I had to overcome has not only given me the experience to brave any future unforeseen circumstances that may arise but also given me the self confidence that one would require to manage a multi faceted operation.", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "6-2008", "experiences/4/jobLocationCountry": "TH", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "12-2002", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQG7fD9pNcGDqQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631309104394?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=XzrZYD6J0NbUCcN7EZquQdrKTTofeF0-cQpJCfrqmds", "experiences/4/title": "Director of Club Operations", "experiences/5/companyName": "Bintan Lagoon Golf & Beach Resort", "experiences/5/jobDescription": "Customer Service Manager: June 1998 – September 1998\nDue to further integration of the management services of the whole resort, my position was then re-designated to that of Customer Service Manager. Reporting directly to the Group Deputy General Manager, who also acts as the General Manager of the integrated resort, I handled all customer enquiries and complaints, sat on the marketing committee, conducted site inspections for potential clients, assisted the Members Relations Manager in attending to the Resort Members’ needs (1500 members to date) and still retained my previous duty as the Villas Operations Manager. When required, I assisted the Rooms Division Manager in the daily operations of the Front Office for the hotel rooms.\n\nVilla Operations Manager: January 1998 – June 1998\nReporting to the General Manager, I was overall in charge of all aspects of the villa operations from conducting site inspections to potential buyers, ensuring contractual works are completed before handing over villas to owners, managing and maintaining the villas with my team of staff, marketing the villas for rental profits, all front of house operations and liaising between the Resort Owners and the Villa Owners. I also worked closely with the Financial Controller and Legal Council for all financial and contractual issues in relation to the villas’ management agreements and contracts.\n\nVilla Operations Executive: July 1997 – January 1998\nThere is a total of 57 villas (3 and 4 bedrooms villas), 52 of which have been sold to corporations and individuals for personal use and investment. Reporting to the Villa Operations Manager, I was pro-active in the setting up of operational procedures from housekeeping, reservations to arrivals and departures. The position also involved assisting with the handing over of the villas to the new owners, liaising with the contractors and the project management office, generally ensuring the best interest of both villa owners and Resort Owners.", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "9-1998", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Bintan, Indonesia", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "6-1997", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/title": "Villa Operations Manager & Guest Services Manager", "experiences/6/companyId": "3135", "experiences/6/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/6/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyatt-regency/", "experiences/6/companyName": "Hyatt Regency Singapore", "experiences/6/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/6/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:3135", "experiences/6/companyWebsite": "http://www.regency.hyatt.com", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "Assistant Guest Services Manager (Regency Club): Feb 1996 – July 1997\nAfter my attachment with the Reservations Department, I was promoted to Assistant Manager in the Regency Club. This involved managing a team of 20 Guest Services Officers in all the 8 Regency Club floors, ensuring everything ran smoothly and assisted the Manager with projects and staff training.\n\nReservations Officer: July 1995 – February 1996\nI was given the opportunity to expand my knowledge of the hotel industry when I was transferred to the Reservations Department. During my brief attachment (8 months), I learned the mechanics of room bookings, the importance of obtaining and giving the correct information prior to guests’ arrivals, the different rate structures, booking sources and inventory control. I also worked closely with the Sales and Marketing team and conduct sales calls to companies in Singapore.\n\nGuest Services Officer (Regency Club): April 1994 – June 1995\nRegency Club features the concept of a “hotel within a hotel”. Guests booked for this category of suite rooms, comprised mostly of top level business executives, are accorded personalized services from point of arrival and departure. My role encompassed most areas of Front Office, from check-in to check-out, providing concierge services, entertaining guests during daily breakfast and cocktail hours in the private Regency Club lounge, to supervising room attendants and butlers on duty.", "experiences/6/jobEndedOn": "6-1997", "experiences/6/jobLocation": "Singapore", "experiences/6/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "4-1994", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/6/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHxxxt3xp9aqw/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1696278108013?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=RY-u9Lsmb9D1NMjvfMcefRST5qtvFJ06QS5h9Rcu8oE", "experiences/6/title": "Assistant Guest Services Manager", "experiences/7/companyId": "1887052", "experiences/7/companyIndustry": "Airlines and Aviation", "experiences/7/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/singapore-airlines/", "experiences/7/companyName": "Singapore Airlines", "experiences/7/companySize": "10001-0", "experiences/7/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:1887052", "experiences/7/companyWebsite": "http://singaporeair.com/", "experiences/7/jobDescription": "The dream of most young girls, I started my career in the hospitality industry as a Flight Attendant. I went through intensive customer service training, grooming course, basic food and beverage skills, first aid and fire fighting to provide superb in-flight service that other airlines talk about, and ensure safety of passengers on both international and domestic routes.", "experiences/7/jobEndedOn": "4-1994", "experiences/7/jobLocationCountry": "SG", "experiences/7/jobStartedO